how do i get cat hair off my clothes when i wash them i have long haired cats and they get hair everywhere including on all of my clothes but even when i wash my clothes the hair doesn't come off is there a trick to get the hair to come off in the washer or dryer i have two kitties one black and one white so i'm doomed everything i wear shows hair lol first embrace the fact that you are going to have some hair on your clothes and just say love me love my cats on the clothes that show a lot of hair use a sticky lint brush to remove the hair before washing before you take it off brush the item quickly takes a few seconds make sure you keep your dirty clothes in a place where the kitties don't go to keep as much hair off as possible increase the amount of times you vacuum and sweep and don't forget to vacuum your furniture keep kitties clean by grooming them regularly i brush mine regularly and it really helps when you put something on check it quickly for cat hair and give it a quick once over with the lint brush i keep one in my closet on a shelf and another by the back door these things will cut it down a lot but not entirely Upholstery Washing machine Brush Dry cleaning Clothing Roomba Japanese tea ceremony The Amber Spyglass Textile manufacturing Characters in the Smurfs Hamster RuneScape quests Bedbug My Little Pony Hair (musical) Grunge music Shadowcat Pitaten Mattress Customs and etiquette of Japan Carnivorous plant Tooth Menstrual cycle Niddah Felis sapiens Fecal incontinence Car washing techniques Professional wrestling match types Cat Vacuum cleaner Social rule Kilt The Cure Trailer Park Boys Sento Dairy Strap-on dildo Guinea pig Ferret Codename: Kids Next Door Mud People Dog training Badly Drawn Kitties Aladdin (1992 film) Changeroom Comanche 2000 Australian Grand Prix Violin The Marriage of Figaro Kodocha Eric Cartman Bong Hearts (game) Little Britain Rastafari movement Certified Nursing Assistant Spirit rover timeline for 2004 March Cruising (maritime) Ne